    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pot with the <strong>remaining softened onion </strong>to a medium heat and add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>ground paprika </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and 700ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [910ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until the potato is fork-tender</p>",
